summary: The document is a classified material review form associated with the House Select Committee on Assassinations (HSCA) staff members' examination of CIA-controlled documents regarding the assassination of President John F. Kennedy. It details the review of classified material at CIA headquarters, notes on accountable pages within the folder, and stresses the importance of document accountability, prohibiting copying or removal. The document also references the CIA Historical Review Program and its approval for release in 1993 under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
key_findings: The document is part of the release under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It contains notes on classified material reviewed by HSCA staff members at CIA headquarters.
The document underscores the strict handling and accountability of the contained materials, with explicit instructions against copying or removing documents.
Mentions the CIA Historical Review Program and indicates the document was approved for release in 1993.
